"title": "7703: apologetics",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7703: apologetics",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The art of explaining the faith in such a way as to make a reasoned defence against its detractors. Paul's Areopagus sermon is a classic example of biblical apologetics, which can be of value to all who are called upon to defend the faith today.</p>\n<h2>Paul's Areopagus sermon, a classic example of biblical apologetics</h2>\n<h3>Paul speaks to his listeners on their own ground, starting on their own terms</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:22-Acts17:23\">ACT 17:22–17:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Paul presents the Christian position</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24-Acts17:27\">ACT 17:24–17:27</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Paul supports his argument in a culturally appropriate way</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:28\">ACT 17:28</a></strong> <em>Paul quotes from two secular writers, first from the Cretan poet Epimenides, and secondly from the Cilician poet Aratus.</em></p>\n<h3>Paul concludes his argument and calls for a response</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:29-Acts17:31\">ACT 17:29–17:31</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Apologetics as a regular feature of Paul's ministry</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:4\">ACT 18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:26-Acts9:30\">ACT 9:26–9:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:19\">ACT 18:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8-Acts19:10\">ACT 19:8–19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:17-Acts28:31\">ACT 28:17–28:31</a></p>\n<h2>Apologetics is part of the work of church leaders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9\">TIT 1:9</a></strong></p>\n<h2>All Christians share responsibility for the task of apologetics</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15\">1PE 3:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Other examples of Christians engaging in apologetics</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:28\">ACT 18:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:14-Acts2:41\">ACT 2:14–2:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:8-Acts6:10\">ACT 6:8–6:10</a></p>\n<h2>Apologetics alone is an inadequate way of presenting the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17-1Cor1:25\">1CO 1:17–1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:1-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:1–2:5</a></p>",
